<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Coding Buddy</title>
  <!-- Import Raleway from Google Fonts -->
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Raleway:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <!-- Bootstrap Icons CSS -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.10.5/font/bootstrap-icons.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/resources/css/homePage.css"></head>
<body>
  <header class = "carousel-header">
    <div class="carousel">
      <img src="../../../img/home/home1.jpg" alt="Header Image 1">
      <img src="../../../img/home/home2.jpg" alt="Header Image 2">
      <img src="../../../img/home/home3.avif" alt="Header Image 3">
      <img src="../../../img/home/home4.jpg" alt="Header Image 4">
      <a href="#" class="prev">&#10094;</a>
      <a href="#" class="next">&#10095;</a>
    </div>
    <div class="header-content">
      <h1>Coding Buddy</h1>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="main-content">
    <div class="slogan">
      <p>For students who are struggling to learn how to code. Coding Buddy is an online tool that makes learning to code SO FUN. Unlike Quizlet or LeetCode, our product is collaborative.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Content with Alternating Rows -->
    <div class="container">
      <!-- Row 1 -->
      <div class="row">
        <div class="text-box">
          <h2><i class="bi bi-flag"></i> Mission</h2>
          <p>Coding Buddy is an online tool targeted towards up and coming computer science students to help them learn and improve their knowledge on a vast majority of computer science topics. We believe that tailoring learning to the individual is the most effective method to achieve mastery of a subject. That is why learning on Coding Buddy takes into account your own personal pre-requisite knowledge.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <div class="image-box">
          <img src="../../../img/home/table1.webp" alt="Row 1 Image">
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Row 2 -->
      <div class="row">
        <div class="text-box">
          <h2><i class="bi bi-gear"></i> How it works</h2>
          <p>Coding Buddy's learning algorithm is targeted to primarily focus on topics and concepts that you personally struggle with. This is through our MC test system which identifies which question you get incorrect and then tailors practice questions and learning flashcards to your needs.</p>
          <p>To get started, navigate over to the MC Test tab and complete the test. After you finish, your score as well as the questions you answered correctly and incorrectly will be recorded. It will then give you feedback on what topics in particular you should focus more on. You can then navigate either to the flashcards or coding questions tab to practice the concepts you got incorrect. These questions will be tailored specifically to the outcome of your test and once you feel confident, you can retake the test to solidify your mastery of the topic.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <div class="image-box">
          <img src="../../../img/home/table2.jpg" alt="Row 2 Image">
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Row 3: To-Do Section -->
      <div class="row">
        <div class="text-box">
          <h2><i class="bi bi-star"></i> To-Do</h2>
          
          <!-- MC Test Section -->
          <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
            <!-- Fixed-width container for the label -->
            <div style="width: 300px; font-weight: bold; white-space: nowrap;">
              MC Test Questions Completed: {{mcPercentage}}%
            </div>
            <!-- Progress bar container -->
            <div class="progress ms-3" style="flex-grow: 1; height: 20px; border-radius: 10px;">
              <div class="progress-bar bg-warning" role="progressbar" style="width: {{mcPercentage}}%;" 
                  aria-valuenow="{{mcPercentage}}" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Practice Problems Section -->
          <div class="d-flex align-items-center">
            <!-- Fixed-width container for the label -->
            <div style="width: 300px; font-weight: bold; white-space: nowrap;">
              Practice Problems Completed: {{codingPercentage}}%
            </div>
            <!-- Progress bar container -->
            <div class="progress ms-3" style="flex-grow: 1; height: 20px; border-radius: 10px;">
              <div class="progress-bar bg-warning" role="progressbar" style="width: {{codingPercentage}}%;" 
                  aria-valuenow="{{codingPercentage}}" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"></div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <div class="image-box">
          <img src="../../../img/home/toDo.jpg" alt="Row 3 Image">
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Row 4: Leaderboard -->
      <div class="row">
        <div class="text-box">
          <h2><i class="bi bi-lightning-charge"></i> Leaderboard</h2>
          <div class="podium-container">
            <!-- Second Place -->
            <div class="podium-box podium-second">
              <div class="podium-position">2</div>
              <div class="podium-info">
                {{#if topUsers.[1]}}
                  <div class="username">{{topUsers.[1].username}}</div>
                  <div class="points">{{topUsers.[1].points}} pts</div>
                {{else}}
                  <div class="username">--</div>
                  <div class="points">0 pts</div>
                {{/if}}
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- First Place -->
            <div class="podium-box podium-first">
              <div class="podium-position">1</div>
              <div class="podium-info">
                {{#if topUsers.[0]}}
                  <div class="username">{{topUsers.[0].username}}</div>
                  <div class="points">{{topUsers.[0].points}} pts</div>
                {{else}}
                  <div class="username">--</div>
                  <div class="points">0 pts</div>
                {{/if}}
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Third Place -->
            <div class="podium-box podium-third">
              <div class="podium-position">3</div>
              <div class="podium-info">
                {{#if topUsers.[2]}}
                  <div class="username">{{topUsers.[2].username}}</div>
                  <div class="points">{{topUsers.[2].points}} pts</div>
                {{else}}
                  <div class="username">--</div>
                  <div class="points">0 pts</div>
                {{/if}}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <div class="image-box">
          <img src="../../../img/home/trophy.jpg" alt="Row 4 Image">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script>
    //Carousel functionality code
  let currentIndex = 0;
  const images = document.querySelectorAll('.carousel img');
  const totalImages = images.length;
  let timer; // Declare timer here

  function showImage(index) {
  images.forEach((img, i) => {
    img.classList.toggle('active', i === index);
  });
  }

  function nextImage() {
  currentIndex = (currentIndex + 1) % totalImages;
  showImage(currentIndex);
  }

  function prevImage() {
  currentIndex = (currentIndex - 1 + totalImages) % totalImages;
  showImage(currentIndex);
  }

  // Function to reset the timer
  function resetTimer() {
  clearInterval(timer);
  timer = setInterval(nextImage, 5000);
  }

  document.querySelector('.carousel a.next').addEventListener('click', function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();
  nextImage();
  resetTimer();
  });

  document.querySelector('.carousel a.prev').addEventListener('click', function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();
  prevImage();
  resetTimer();
  });

  // Initialize timer to change images every 5 seconds
  timer = setInterval(nextImage, 5000);
  showImage(currentIndex);
  </script>
  <script src="/js/index.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>